cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the analysis of natural disasters using images posted on social media platforms. The proposed approach involves content-based image retrieval and relevance feedback. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the processing of large amounts of data and the evaluation of the proposed approach, which could also make it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
